t.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test reports**\\n\\nI think the tests might not be in the report because they failed, which means they weren't run. It's not necessary to run them again, but we could fix any potential Checkstyle line length issues. It seems like Checkstyle might have failed before the tests were run, causing no coverage to be reported. I need to check the existing project style, which might have a maximum line length of 100 characters.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Debugging the code**\\n\\nAlright, I'm considering whether I need to include `serialPersistentFields`. But it seems I shouldn't. I should test the error related to `assertParameters`, which compares `ECParameterSpec.getCurve().equals`. I'm wondering if `EllipticCurve` is returning true when it shouldn't, maybe indicating a deeper issue. I need to look into that to ensure everything's functioning correctly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FjSLsSuIozHTQLfrCvJZ86k4|fc_0c452323a1efbc39016a25fa6468e48196b2f1899e6b9275f2", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport json\np='tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json'\nwith open(p) as f:j=json.load(f)\nfor name in ['org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.JCEECPrivateKey','org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.JCEDHPublicKey']:\n  for c in j['classes']:\n    if c['className']==name:\n      print(name,c['coveredCalls'],c['totalCalls'])\n      for s in c['callSites']: print(s)\nPY", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 406, "output": 2329, "cacheRead": 59904, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 62639, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780873775420, "responseId": "resp_0c452323a1efbc39016a25fa300a848196af2508053a0a9c88"}}
